## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. **Backend API Testing**: After starting the backend (`cd e:\allen-task2\backend && npm run start:dev`), test each endpoint with curl/browser:
   - `POST /api/auth/signup` with body `{"name":"Test","email":"test@test.com","password":"123456"}`
   - `POST /api/auth/login` with body `{"email":"test@test.com","password":"123456"}`  
   - `GET /api/products`, `POST /api/products`, `PATCH /api/products/1`, `DELETE /api/products/1`
   - Same for customers and orders
   - `GET /api/seed` to verify seeding works

2. **Frontend Build Check**: Run `cd e:\allen-task2\frontend && npm run build` — should compile without errors.

### Browser Testing
3. **Full E2E Flow in Browser** (after starting both servers):
   - Open `http://localhost:3000/login` → Signup → Login → Verify redirect to dashboard
   - Check dashboard stats cards show correct counts
   - Navigate to Products → Add, Edit, Delete a product
   - Navigate to Customers → Add, Edit, Delete a customer
   - Navigate to Orders → Create, Edit, Delete an order
   - Test sidebar navigation and logout
   - Resize browser to verify responsive design (mobile & tablet)

### Manual Verification
4. **User Manual Testing**: After implementation, you can test the full flow by:
   - Run `cd e:\allen-task2\backend && npm run start:dev` (backend on port 3001)
   - Run `cd e:\allen-task2\frontend && npm run dev` (frontend on port 3000)
   - Open `http://localhost:3000` in browser and test all CRUD operations
